article.headline: New Hampshire 28, Maine 24
article.story: ORONO, Maine -- R.J. Toman passed for 127 yards and two touchdowns to lift New Hampshire to a 28-24 win over Maine on Saturday. Chad Kackert rushed for 89 yards, including first-half touchdowns of 46 and 18 yards, for New Hampshire. The team's quick-strike offense came up with a methodical 11-play, 79-yard scoring drive late in the fourth quarter to seal the victory. The Wildcats (9-2, 6-2 Colonial Athletic Association) overcame a snow-covered Morse Field and cold, windy conditions to upend the Black Bears. Maine (8-4, 5-3 CAA) had its six-game winning streak snapped. The Wildcats took the lead when Mike Boyle took a short screen pass near the right sideline, eluded two potential tacklers and tiptoed into the end zone with 3:27 remaining for his first of two touchdowns. Linebacker Matt Parent led the New Hampshire defense with 12 tackles, while Maine's Sean Wasson and Andrew Downey had 17 and 12 tackles, respectively. Maine had two more possessions in the final 3 1/2 minutes, but Terrence Klein intercepted quarterback Mike Brusko twice to help New Hampshire secure the win. Brusko led Maine with 65 rushing yards, including a 1-yard scoring dive. He also completed 6-of-15 passes for 98 yards.
